The '''2008 La Flèche Wallonne''' [[cycling race]] took place on April 23, 2008 and was won by [[Luxembourg]]er [[Kim Kirchen]] of {{ct|THR|2008a}}. It was the 72nd running of the [[La Flèche Wallonne]] and covered {{convert|199.5|km|mi}} between [[Charleroi]] and [[Huy]] in [[Belgium]] in 4 hours, 35 minutes and 20 seconds. [[Australia]]n [[Cadel Evans]] of {{ct|SIL|2008}} and [[Italy|Italian]] [[Damiano Cunego]] of {{ct|LAM|2008}} came second and third respectively.

