{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}
The '''Telangana Cricket Association''' is the governing body of the [[cricket]] activities in the State of [[Telangana]] in [[India]]. It has its Head-quarters in Somajiguda, [[Hyderabad]], Telangana.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tcricket.in/Default.aspx|title=Telangana Cricket Association|publisher=Tcricket|access-date=8 April 2018}}</ref>

==Associate Membership Status==
The Telangana Cricket Association (TCA) applied for Associate Membership of [[Board of Control for Cricket in India]] citing the inadequate representation and opportunities for players outside of [[Hyderabad]] under already existing [[Hyderabad Cricket Association]] (HCA).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/cricket/telangana-cricket-association-request-associate-member-status-from-bcci/story-5M86k8MNfLrFCk0e6FPxYP.html|title=Telangana Cricket Association request associate member status from BCCI|publisher=hindustantimes.com|access-date=10 May 2018|date=11 May 2018}}</ref> On May 4, Bombay High Court directed Committee of Administrators (CoA) of BCCI to hear and decide the plea by TCA within six weeks (before June 15, 2018).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mid-day.com/articles/bombay-high-court-urges-coa-look-into-telanganas-membership-appeal/19411184|title=Bombay High Court Urges CoA Look Into Telangana's Membership Appeal|publisher=mid-day.com|access-date=29 May 2018|date=11 May 2018}}</ref>

On May 30, 2018, TCA representatives met CoA of BCCI at its headquarters as per their invitation and presented their case on associate membership of TCA.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://telanganatoday.com/bcci-coa-invites-telangana-cricket-association-for-a-meeting-on-may-30|title=BCCI CoA invites Telangana Cricket Association for a meeting on May 30|publisher=telanganatoday.com|access-date=29 May 2018|date=21 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://telanganatoday.com/tca-presents-their-case-to-coa-members|title=TCA presents their case to CoA members|publisher=telanganatoday.com|access-date=31 May 2018|date=30 May 2018}}</ref>

