{{italic title}} {{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}} {{Use British English|date=June 2016}} '''''The Ball of Fortune''''' is a 1926 [[Cinema of the United Kingdom|British]] [[silent film|silent]] [[sports film]] directed by [[Hugh Croise]] and starring [[Billy Meredith]], [[James Knight (actor)|James Knight]] and [[Mabel Poulton]].<ref>http://ftvdb.bfi.org.uk/sift/title/142731</ref> Based on the 1925 novel ''[[The Ball of Fortune (novel)|The Ball of Fortune]]'' by [[Sydney Horler]], the film is set against the backdrop of [[Professionalism in association football|professional football]]. Top player [[Billy Meredith]] appears as himself.
