{{Infobox football club | clubname = West Kenya Sugar | image = | fullname = West Kenya Sugar Football Club | nickname = | founded = 2007 | ground = [[Bukhungu Stadium]] | capacity = 5,000 | chairman = | mgrtitle = Head coach | manager = Nelson Simwa | league = [[Kenyan National Super League]] | season = [[2013 FKF Division One|2013]] | position = [[FKF Division One]] }} '''West Kenya Sugar Football Club''' is an [[association football]] club based in [[Kakamega]], [[Kenya]]. The club currently competes in the [[Kenyan National Super League]].<ref>http://www.soccervista.com/St_Joseph_FC-West_Kenya_Sugar-1675852-1675852.html</ref> The club was known as '''Kabrass United Football Club''' until July 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.futaa.com/football/article/why-west-kenya-ditched-the-atribal-taga |title=Why West Kenya ditched the 'tribal tag' |author=Wilson Mathu |publisher=Futaa.com |date=6 July 2012 |accessdate=15 July 2012}}</ref>
==History== The club was founded in 2007 by Matthew Dane Norman and [[Antony Golec]], and has an association with [[Aldershot Town F.C.]]
==Stadium== The team currently plays its home games at the 5,000-capacity [[Bukhungu Stadium]].
